---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="ScrapeConvert - Terms" description="ScrapeConvert is free and open source under the MIT license, provided as is, and you are responsible for how you use it.">
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 prose-invert">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-accent-400">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-50 sm:text-4xl">Terms</h1>
    <p class="mt-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
      These are the plain-language terms for using ScrapeConvert.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-100">Free and open source</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
      ScrapeConvert is free to use and open source under the MIT license. You are welcome to read the source, run your own copy, and adapt it within the terms of that license.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-100">Provided as is</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
      The tool is provided as is, with no warranty of any kind. We do our best to keep it working and safe, but we cannot promise it will always be available or that it will fit every use. You use it at your own risk.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-100">You are responsible for what you scrape and how you use it</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
      You decide which sites you point ScrapeConvert at and what you do with the images you pull. You are responsible for respecting the rights of the sites and the owners of those images, and for using the results in a way that is lawful and fair. If you are not sure you have the right to use an image, do not use it.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-12">
      <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 font-mono text-sm text-accent-300 transition-colors duration-150 hover:text-accent-400">
        Back home
      </a>
    </p>
  </main>
</Base>
